text: This is a client mod, stripping down Minecraft to what is basically a Creative mode with only redstone-related blocks available. Like most client mods, it requires you to inject some files into minecraft.jar, but it works in a separate directory so you can update your main Minecraft program files afterward without issue. Because it is a client mod, redstone behaves exactly as it does in the regular game. It can load and save circuits to schematics, and you can build your schematics with most of blocks available in-game.

Command-line, very customizable output (lots of options), capable of rendering huge maps. Also works under Wine (after adding a DLL override). AlphaVespucci GUI has been written in .NET by LrdPhoenix.
A simulator for Redstone circuits. Place circuit elements in a grid and use Play/Pause to control the simulation. Repeaters are not implemented.

This program stores and displays an inventory of all blocks and items in Minecraft, their data values, and suggested trading-post values. The table can be sorted just like Windows Explorer sorts files and can be searched with an internal window that pops up upon selection or pressing Ctrl+F. There is also a Value Calculator that comes up upon selection or pressing Ctrl+Q, which helps you work out how much one item is worth, as compared to another.
The first mapper for infinite levels. Created for Infdev levels before it became Alpha.
A redstone simulator in the spirit of Baezon's program, written from scratch. Includes repeaters. Loading and saving has not yet been implemented.
A simulator capable of imitating the redstone and piston mechanics from Minecraft. It is a fork of Simnik's Circuit Simulator (above)
A fork of Rek's Circuit Simulator (above). Adds several blocks, including rails (but no minecarts).
Converts a Dwarf Fortress level to a Minecraft Alpha world according to a ruleset.
DSwitch is a simple texture pack installer & managing program with a couple of extra nifty features.

The Original Minecraft Speedhack For Classic Minecraft. Previous versions used to work For 1.6 and Down. This Is Possibly Able to work With MONO for mac(Has Not Been Tested) This speedhack Was Originally Created in February, 2011
Easily switch your world game mode between Survival and Creative.
Simple Minecraft inventory editor for OS X and Linux.
The first of its kind. Creates an isometric image of a Classic level.
This the easiest way to read/edit your lastlogin file. In the lastlogin file is the username and the password saved
Save editor. Edit world time, spawn/player position, health and inventory. Does not run with Mono.
Features: delete chunks; copy and paste chunks (works between worlds); generate large pine trees.
Opening up code for community development. Captures position packets using ngrep and feeds the packet to the php to map.
Creates and Loads multiple versions of minecraft without Using The Normal Minecraft Files, Now Updates using normal Minecraft GameUpdater in Program.
Type in how much things you need to smelt, press "Check" and it will show you how much fuel you need
A web-based inventory editor. Upload your data files, edit, and download. Still adding features.
A 3D exporter which aims to export all geometry, not just cubic blocks.
Gives you a little boost/speedhack when you click the button.
Quick and easy floor planner. Can export files for others to open and edit.
Command-line editor derived from MCEdit. Works well with servers.
A dungeon generator seemingly inspired by old Roguelike games. Creates rooms and levels out of different materials, in different styles. Rooms may hold traps, statues, enemy spawns, and/or treasure.
Launcher wrapper allowing multiple servers to be retained and accessed in a simple manner.

A command-line inventory editor, with additional features including switching between creative/adventure, moving the spawn point, changing time of day, bookmarking locations. showing the world random seed, controlling the weather, lose-me, and more.
Lightweight texture-pack installer with the ability to install from a ZIP, direct URL or from a built-in library of submitted packs.
Interactive graph showing material counts to height based on a Minecraft save game directory.
Pepijn de Vos, Victor Engmark, Alejandro Aguilera
Calculates how much goods you need to craft the amount of items you want or how much fuel you need to smelt the amount of ores you want.

Minecraft Assist Utility currently features a game launcher and robust back up system that is both easy to configure and painless to use! Designed for syncing save game between multiple computers. Has proper error handling, unique time saving back up system, game launcher supports multiple browsers as well as the standalone. Updated constantly!
Minecraft Backup is a simple Windows Application that will backup your Minecraft Files. It has the ability to customize what you want to backup. Now with automated backups & Dropbox Support

A simple backup + restore tool with automatic map image generation. Includes AlphaVespucci but you can configure it to use any mapper (settings for c10t are also provided). Full source project available for download. Programmed using Lua and AutoPlay Media Studio Personal Edition.
Minecraft Block ID Program for Classic
Get any Minecraft Classic ID by typing in its name.
Select a specific item from the drop-down lists, and the application will display the recipe & materials needed to create it.
Searchable Item/Block ID list. Searches as you type, displaying items or blocks which have those letters in them.
Provides in-game updates of the players position. Also allows bookmarking of positions to navigate back to.

An iOS application that will help you with your adventures in Minecraft. It features a very clean interface and it shows all the items found in the game. Minecraft Helper also has a favorite function, the crafting recipes are interactive and there are links to this Wiki on all item and block profiles, which open in-app. According to the developers also coming to Android soon.
An interactive ID list that allows you to search through blocks and items.
Select an item from the drop-down lists and click 'Get ID' to display its item ID.
Generates terrain based on user-defined terrain functions. Includes a GUI with map preview.
Minecraft Modding Tool is a advanced tool which can download latest mods, view tutorials within the program, view servers download texture packs and much more. Website is now dead.
Save your favorite multiplayer server addresses and connects Minecraft directly on to the server.
Calculates the distance needed to create a railway between two points, as well as how many materials are needed (Now including Powered Rails, Detector Rails, and Boosters).

A small launcher tool that will back up and synchronize your saved games across multiple computers, performing file operations both before and after Minecraft is launched. It's meant to be a zero-effort tool so you don't have to go through the pain of loading your saved games from a USB drive or cloud folder.

An easy to use 'save manager' which effectively gives you the power to have an unlimited amount of worlds! Use this great tool to move saved worlds between a holding area and the real minecraft area. This makes it easy for modders because it can move worlds into an easily accessible directory and then back again in two clicks!

Java Swing-based GUI for Minecraft players to backup and restore their valuable saves. Designed to be extremely easy to use, it auto-locates your local Minecraft 'saves' directory, and remembers the location of your backup directory and last backed up World. In many cases, the user can backup or restore in just one click!

A much more convenient way of dealing with the standard server.properties of a traditional Minecraft server. Allows you to save and load your configurations to easily switch between worlds, and even includes some basic server backup and worldfile seed reading capabilities.
Displays servers from servers.minecraftforum.net and helps you managing favorites.
MTC is a tool used to manage terrain.png textures quickly and easily. This includes replacement of existing textures by new ones, exporting textures, and generation of the modified terrain.png.
Minecraft Texture Mover makes it super easy (drag & drop) to get textures into Minecraft for mac. It is no longer available on the Mac App Store.
Allows you to switch texture packs.
Change the time of a world. Works on mac with Mono.

Minecrafter is a mod manager with a twist. Instead of providing simple merging tools, Minecrafter allows you to "craft" your own mods by mixing and matching other people's mods, all without touching JARs or graphics programs. The program is discontinued, but the source was released, and the the program continues to function with new versions of minecraft.

A map viewer / concept design for Android OS. Use your own 1.3 beta (and up) levels, temporarily build and destroy blocks, sensor steering, crouch & jump, no-clip mode. Works on low end devices (requires android 2.1 or higher). may contain bugs.

All-in-one Editor. Includes a terrain editor similar to Omen and NBT Forge. Replaces blocks of one type with another. Also lets you edit your player's inventory and the world's entities. Since the November 21 Update, the terrain editor seems to be missing, but other problems have been fixed, and the program has been updated to support all blocks and objects added in the Halloween Update. [1]
Share your natural maps and occurrences as a string of 50 chars.
Lets you play and save Minecraft on the cloud (i.e. Dropbox). Useful for taking Minecraft saves anywhere you go.
Intuitive GUI for creating detailed, zoomable map renders of you Minecraft worlds. Powered by Tectonicus, Minetographer is fast and easy to use.
3D, Slices by clicking, GUI, Customizable Schemes. Connects to SMP servers.
Installs graphics packs and other mods for Alpha. Can detect the structure of mods inside zip files, allowing for one-click installation in most cases.

Installs mods by simply drag,drop & click method. Compatible with every ZIP-packed mod.(mods in other archive types need to be repackaged). Also compatible with texture packs. In other words, this program adds to minecraft.jar everything you want it to add.
A successor to Omen that supports the newer Alpha levels. Like Omen, you can view 2d slices and paint blocks using a different set of brushes. Added the new Blocks of the Halloween Update.
Edit every NBT File including your level.dat (Health, Items) or chunks. More features planned.

The first map editor, created to edit Indev and later Classic levels. You can view the level's blocks in 2d slices, and alter them by "painting" blocks using brushes of different shapes and sizes. Also includes some terrain generators and supports the old Indev levels. Requires minecraft-server.jar for Classic support.
Online Minecraft Inventory Editor for any platform, any browser.
Part of the mcservers:OpenCraft project. A Java library and standalone tool to provide visualizations for all save formats.
Highly customizable with a lot of options. Supports both GUI and command line and have the ability to use multiple cores (multithreading). Example render.
Command-line, suitable for cronjobs or scripts.
Displays a list of Item names and IDs for any entry containing the text entered.
GUI that allows you to easily preview, package, and switch texture packs.
A quick and easy way to change your spawnpoint! Just select a world, change spawn, and press Save!

Speeds up your system clock, which in turn speeds up in-game time. Works for both Singleplayer and multiplayer. Requires .NET v2, and may work in Linux (or Mac) with Mono.
Does not work with Beta 1.6+, because Mojang fixed this.
The app can manage multiple backups and is capable of repairing/replacing chunk errors or corrupted savegames. Updated frequently.
GUI for c10t, includes single and batch processing.
Creates wild, surreal landscapes of several varieties.

texts.text: A repository for outdated programs, defined as being more than one major version behind the current release. Anything that has not been updated for the full release of Minecraft is moved here. Note that some of these programs may still work with newer versions of Minecraft, but have not been clearly marked as such by their authors.
